<div id="article">
<PRE>

My baby&rsquo;s got the blues again, and everyone&rsquo;s the same
We&rsquo;re falling over backwards trying to play their game
Which is in and out of vision like beyond a picture frame
We're silly little children, we forget we are to blame
Ch: Oh............................... there&rsquo;s a battle in Britain,
  Oh ............................... there&rsquo;s a battle all over the world
  And it&rsquo;s a shame

Kaleidoscopic hairdos go with kaleidoscopic eyes
And we&rsquo;re really so together, never taking sides,
Yet we&rsquo;re from a popular pattern, and we say no strings or ties
But I can feel hands in strangle holds a-making us want to cry
Ch:
 .......... oh for shame

All I hear is hear security and how we must hang on
When everyone&rsquo;s against us - who is right and who is wrong
Where it makes no sense to tell your truth if you just come on too strong
But I can hear those bully boys cranking up the same old song
Ch:
 ............oh it&rsquo;s a shame
</PRE>

